## 🚀 Setup From Scratch

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A([1\nPython 3.10+]) --> B([2\nInstall uv])
    B --> C([3\nInstall\nDatabricks CLI])
    C --> D([4\nAuth Login])
    D --> E([5\nFind Endpoint])
    E --> F([6\nConfigure .env])
    F --> G([7\nuv sync])
    G --> H([8\nRun App ✅])

    style A fill:#e8f5e9,color:#333
    style H fill:#c8e6c9,color:#333
```

### Step 1 — Python
```bash
python --version   # Need 3.10+
```

### Step 2 — Install uv
```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy ByPass -c "irm https://astral.sh/uv/install.ps1 | iex"
```
```bash
uv --version
```

### Step 3 — Install Databricks CLI
```bash
pip install databricks-cli
databricks --version
```

> ⚠️ If not recognized, add your Python Scripts folder to PATH:
> ```bash
> python -c "import sysconfig; print(sysconfig.get_path('scripts'))"
> ```

### Step 4 — Authenticate
```bash
databricks auth login
```
```
# When prompted — use ONLY the base URL
Databricks host: https://adb-3423511784067605.5.azuredatabricks.net
```

```bash
# Verify it worked
databricks current-user me
```

### Step 5 — Find Your Endpoint
```bash
databricks serving-endpoints list
# Note the "name" field from the output
```

### Step 6 — Configure .env
```env
DATABRICKS_MODEL_ENDPOINT=databricks-claude-sonnet-4-5
LLM_TEMPERATURE=0.1
INPUT_FOLDER=data/input
OUTPUT_FOLDER=data/output
ORDERS_FILE=data/orders/orders.json
```

> ✅ Correct: `databricks-claude-sonnet-4-5`
> ❌ Wrong: `system.ai.databricks-claude-sonnet-4-5`

### Step 7 — Install Dependencies
```bash
uv sync --all-extras
```

### Step 8 — Run
```bash
uv run python -m core.main --file
```

